definition:
A man of the tribe of Benjamin living at the time of United Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Ch.8.35; 
 son of: Micah (H4318H); 
 brother of: Pithon (H6377), Melech (H4429) and Ahaz (H0271H); also called Tahrea at 1Ch.9.41; 
Another name of ta.a.re.a (תַּאֲרֵעַ "Tarea" H8390) 
 § Tahrea = "cunning"
 a Benjamite, son of Micah in the line of Saul
